Jason,

Haven't done the ones on my 78 yet, but did do my 79 convertible.

Just buy new bearings and count on a day of it.
If they wiggle that much, then you are going to need to replace them 
anyway.  Cheap insurance for another 100,000+ miles.



Cheers, dave


