> Hi Folks,
> 
> I've been noticing a ~CLUNK~ type noise coming from the right-rear of my 
> 1979 Westy when I go over bumps, and checked it out yesterday.  I pulled off 
> the wheel and unbolted the brake drum, and was able to move the stub axle 
> in-and-out about 1/8" by hand.  That would explain the ~CLUNK~ noise!
> 
> Obviously, it's something to do with the bearings, but what?  Do they just 
> need repacking with grease and readjusting?  Or, do I need to remove the 
> entire assembly and replace the seals and bearings?  It has been doing this 
> for about 3,000 miles.
> 
> I believe one can't adjust rear bearings the same way one can adjust the 
> front.  In addition, I helped a friend with his sag correction and rear 
> bearing replacement on his '71, and agree with the general consensus that 
> Bentley is a pretty poor resource for this job.  Does anybody know of a 
> better resource?  My friend will be helping me, but I'm sure that '71 is 
> different from '79.
> 
> Thanks for any help or suggestions.
